Preconditions:
The arrays `nums` and `cost` must have the same length.
The arrays `nums` and `cost` must not be empty.
The elements in the array `nums` must be integers.
The elements in the array `cost` must be integers.
The elements in the array `cost` must be non-negative.

Postconditions:
The method returns a long value representing the minimum total cost.
All elements in the array `nums` are equal.
The total cost is minimized, meaning that changing any element in the array `nums` to another value would increase the total cost.